elements.text: The Art & History of Dresden, Leipzig & Meiβen
• All excursions, entrance fees & guided tours included
• Direct scheduled British Airways flights from Heathrow to Berli
• Executive coach (as detailed in the itinerary)
• Zwinger Palace & Old Masters Picture Gallery – guided tour
• Pillnitz Castle, Gardens & the Museum of Decorative Arts – guided tour
• Paddle Steamer Cruise from Königstein to Pillnitz
• Royal Palace – Old Green Vault & New Green Vault
• Museum der Bildenden Künste – guided tour

We stay five nights at the centrally located 4* Maritim Hotel (www.maritim.de) in Dresden. Located by the River Elbe, and under a five minute walk from the Semper Opera House, facilities at the hotel include a restaurant, bar, swimming pool, gymnasium, steam room and a sauna. All rooms are en suite and feature television, telephone, hairdryer and a mini bar. Dinner is included in our hotel on the first and second evenings, and at a carefully selected restaurant which is a 10 minute walk from our hotel on the last night. The remaining two evenings are on bed and breakfast basis.
• Local accommodation tax to be paid
Flight details may be subject to change.
Price based on twin share. Minimum numbers required. Normal booking conditions apply.
For more information on this tour contact your Group Organiser
Any air holidays and flights in this brochure are ATOL protected by the Civil Aviation Authority. Tailored Travel’s ATOL number is 5605
The Art & History of Dresden, Leipzig & Meiβen
We meet at Heathrow Airport for our direct scheduled British Airways
flight to Berlin. On arrival in Berlin we are met by our guide and transfer by coach to the centrally located 4* Maritim Hotel in Dresden for a five
night stay. Dinner is included in our hotel the first and second evenings,
Old Masters Picture Gallery and at a carefully selected restaurant on the last night. The remaining
two evenings are on bed and breakfast basis.
Pillnitz Castle, Gardens & the Museum of Decorative Arts Day 2
This morning we enjoy a guided walking tour of Dresden, taking in sights
Paddle Steamer Cruise from such as the Semper Opera House and the Cathedral. During our guided Königstein to Pillnitz
tour we visit the Frauenkirche, an outstanding example of Protestant sacred architecture and featuring one of the largest domes in Europe.
Destroyed during the bombing of Dresden in World War II, the church
was rebuilt after the reunification of Dresden. This afternoon we walk to the Zwinger Palace, the old fortress of Dresden. A guided tour of the Old
Masters Picture Gallery in the Palace introduces us to works by Rubens,
Canaletto, Raphael, Titian, Rembrandt and Vermeer, as well as a
We visit Pillnitz Castle and Gardens for a morning guided tour. One of the
area’s finest summer palaces, the Castle lies picturesquely on the banks
Meißen Porcelain Museum of the River Elbe. With its flying buttresses and chimneys ornamented

with crowns, this is the only Chinese style castle of its size in Europe. Here we visit the Museum of Decorative Arts. The museum focuses on Saxon and European arts and crafts of the 17th and 18th century. This afternoon we travel to Königstein, a town located by the banks of the River Elbe. We then take an included memorable paddle steamer cruise along the River Elbe from Königstein to Pirna to view the splendour of the Saxony Alps.

This morning we visit the Royal Palace and visit the Old Green Vault with its collection of fine silver and jewellery followed by the New Green Vault highlighting some of the central pieces from the collection in their original
setting including the celebrated Dresden Green Diamond. We then visit the New Green Vault. The rest of the day is at leisure in Dresden.

Our guided walking tour of Leipzig this morning takes in sights such as the Opera House and the Nikolaikirche. We also visit the magnificent late-Gothic Tomaskirche, where Bach was the choirmaster from 1723. This afternoon we enjoy a guided tour at the Museum der Bildenden Künste, home to a fine collection of paintings by German masters from the late Middle Ages to the present day. Included are Lucas Cranach, Martin Schongauer, Caspar David Friedrich, Arnold Böcklin, Max Lieberman and Max Klinger. A farewell dinner is included at a carefully
selected restaurant in Dresden this evening.

A guided tour of the Meißen Porcelain Museum this morning gives an insight into the production process at this world renowned manufacturer. We return to Berlin Airport for our direct scheduled British Airways flight back Lacock to Heathrow. Abbey
NB:- Please note we reserve the right to alter the above itinerary if required for operational
reasons. Given the historic nature of the places visited, a certain degree of walking will
be involved, and this holiday may not be suitable for those with mobility problems.
